        Document(
            page_content="When creating a new shift, you can enable Shift Location if you want employees with this shift to only be able to clock in/out at specific locations.\n[Gambar: https://help.nusawork.com/storage/help/images/xcjyzuJc1U3DUqsq7Paek6xNEppRitrSBue4ln5t.png]\n\nLocation Table: Displays a list of locations registered for this shift.  \nNote: Shifts that allow custom location settings will automatically override attendance locations in the workgroup and employees applying this shift.\n[Gambar: https://help.nusawork.com/storage/help/images/n2vNN3vwmmzztTPFOFH78xaUE7buifDbD3NGXfLI.png]\nAdd Location: Click 'Add Location' to add an attendance location to the shift. Then you will be in this page\n[Gambar: https://help.nusawork.com/storage/help/images/hVT8pfmnAxBVPYEnPIpolhZSy3izFJwqFJxQni4B.png]\n\n1. Enter the location name or address in the map search field, then ensure the point on the map is correct.  \nNote: If the location is not detected on the map, use Google Maps search by enabling the toggle button at the top right of the map.\n2. Name the location, e.g., Main Office.\n3. Set the maximum distance employees can clock in/out from the location point. For example, if the maximum distance is set to 100 meters, employees outside a 100-meter radius from the location point will not be able to clock in/out.\n4. Coordinates will be automatically filled in once the location is detected on the map.\n5. Set accuracy tolerance to facilitate location recording if the radius obtained during clock in/out does not meet the required accuracy.  \nNote: Nusawork recommends using an accuracy tolerance of at least more than a 20-meter radius to facilitate the attendance process.\nClick Select Location to save the created location.",
            metadata={"id": 426, "title": "How to Set Shift Location", "url": "https://help.nusawork.com/how-to-set-shift-locations"},
        ),

